TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Stability of Steady States in Perfect Foresight Models
AU  - Laitner, John P.
AB  - [This paper analyzes nonlinear growth models in which agents' expectations have a role in determining present behavior. Assuming agents have perfect foresight, we develop sufficiency conditions for the local stability of a given steady state. We then briefly discuss several examples in which stability prevails.]
C1  - Full publication date: Mar., 1981
DB  - JSTOR
