TY  - JOUR
TI  - Value of Information with Sequential Futures Markets
AU  - Green, Jerry
AB  - [The effects of an improvement in information on the efficiency of risk-bearing are studied under various systems of incomplete markets. With sequential futures markets for uncontingent delivery, the welfare effects are indeterminate in sign, except under special circumstances. In the presence of options markets, however, an improved information structure is almost surely beneficial.]
